**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**
bug

**What is the current behavior?**
Dispatching a *CustomEvent* on an anchor tag (`<a>`) has no effect. 

```javascript
class App extends React.Component {  
  constructor(){
    super();
    this.ref = React.createRef();
  }
  
  componentDidMount() {
    const event = new CustomEvent('custom-event');
    this.ref.current.addEventListener('custom-event', this.onCustomEvent);
    this.ref.current.dispatchEvent(event);
  }
  
  onCustomEvent(e) {
    console.log('Custom event triggered:', e);
  }
  
  render() {
    return (
      <a href="#" ref={this.ref}>link</a>
    );
  }
}

ReactDOM.render(<App />, document.getElementById('container'));
```

Link to jsfiddle: (https://jsfiddle.net/violentPuree/7yf4t1uk/26/)

**Please note:** For some reason when the jsfiddle page initially loads the custom event listener is triggered (This does not happen when the application is run in the browser outside of jsfiddle).
Any subsequent app launch (by clicking on the **Run** in jsfiddle) does not trigger the event listener.
However, if the anchor tag is replaced by any other tag (div, b, button, span, etc.) the listener is correctly triggered every time.

**What is the expected behavior?**
Dispatching a CustomEvent on an anchor tag should work.

**Which versions of React, and which browser / OS are affected by this issue? Did this work in previous versions of React?**

Chrome 71
React 16.7.0, 15.6.0
